<br>
Rotations are about sharing content between those who can kill, making sure said mobs die, and maximizing the loot brought onto the server on a weekly basis.  Guilds that prove themselves capable get to be on said rotations - how is it fair that guilds NOT on a rotation can threaten to risk every or every other spawn of a mob they aren't on rotation for.  Guilds on rotation should see the mob on rotation at least as often as those attempting to get on, especially for mobs that are &quot;wasted&quot; when you try them.  Even on a mob that isn't wasted would wear my patience thin if night after night Guild ABC was keeping us from him by trying him time and again.  Escalate that to a mob that poofs when you fail, and it becomes even more heinous.<br>
<br>
Emp is the same way, so please don't complain how it's just the Big Three trying to keep the up and coming guilds down.  We are about to try Emp.  BotS got to do Emp to their heart's content until they got him right, that is the benefit of being first.  We have more information about the fight than they did, that is the advantage of coming along later.  I shouldn't be allowed to night after night keep popping and wasting chances for Tindi or BotS to get loot off Emp &quot;just cause we think we got it licked this time&quot;.  (Emp isn't wasted per se, but he can only be spawned once every so many hours - thus keeping rotation guilds from trying mobs they have proven they can kill).<br>
<br>
To summarize, I am ok with a change of the Statue rule, but you cannot deny the linkage of the Idol to Statue making any &quot;race&quot; a farce.  However, I will not watch VoF or any guild pop and risk multiple AoWs to NB's one per cycle.   We've proved ourselves, and once you do (not if), you will see things quite a bit differently than you do now.  You will appreciate not having to watch Guild ABC pop and waste 4-5 AoWs in 5-10 spawns so that you get to wait for them to finally kill it before you get to loot him again. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bogarthamule>Bogarthamule</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>VoF</span><br>  Posts: 92<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(12/20/02 4:09:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=410.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AoW and the Guild Rep forum</span><hr size=1> I understand perfectly that rules for rotations are made to help not only current rotation guilds but future ones as well.  I also understand that two wrongs don't make a right...if anything some of us are just frustrated because no one ever brought this particular rule to our attention until we were just about ready to try again (Granted, there needs to be responsibility on boths sides to find out or inform how rotations work, which we didn't do for AoW...instead relying on standard rotation rules and what LoM did thinking it must be ok).<br>
<br>
That's a good point concerning a non-rot guild getting more chances at a mob than a rot guild.  Really, that does not seem fair, but...<br>
<br>
As I pointed out before, I don't think it's fair to use a rule that will eventually be harder on other guilds down the line.  When just BotS, TL, and NB were on the AoW rotation, then a guild trying to get on the rotation would only have to wait 3 spawns to get their shot.  The next guild would have to wait 4.  Now an arguement can be made that getting there first gives them that luxury of not having to wait as long, but when dealing with multiple guilds all getting on rotation around the same time, that issue shouldn't hold up as much (Just look at the additions to the NToV rotation lately...any one of those guilds could have cleared the following week or the previous week...was just chance that the guilds entered in the order they did).<br>
<br>
Even if guild A having to wait 4 spawns, then guild B having to wait 5 spawns, then guild C having to wait 6 is a fair rule...I do NOT think guild J (obviously way down the line) having to wait 13 spawns in between attempts is fair.  Controlling the amount of attempts by how many guilds are on a rotation is not going to be fair to guilds in the future since the rotations will generally always get bigger.  That's the exact reason waiting for Statue turn doesn't work now.  Maybe the fair way NOW would be to use Karadin's point of only trying AoW once per rotation cycle, but that rule will eventually become unfair the way the old rule has become.<br>
<br>
Like I said, the point of non-rot guilds getting more attempts than rot guilds IS an important issue, but setting rules that we KNOW will eventually become unfair will cause problems.  Who's to say how many guilds will need to be on the AoW rot before this idea becomes unfair?  You can bet the first guild this rule actually hurts will be upset because of it.  I really think the most fair rule is one that will not change.  Whether it is 1 spawn between kills or 10 needs to be decided.  Whatever rule is decided, I think it's best to make it so similar problems won't happen in the future. (I think one way of doing this would be to set a &quot;penalty&quot; of sorts for if a guild failed two or maybe three times in a row...then that guild has to wait a month, two months, etc until they can try again...this might make a guild think twice to try everytime the rule allows them to if they just aren't ready yet) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thundaxstormkeeper>Thundax Stormkeeper</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 83<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(12/20/02 7:09:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=410.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AoW and the Guild Rep forum</span><hr size=1> Why should rules that have existed for ages be changed now so that guilds currently trying AoW should have a better chance at getting on the rotation.<br>
<br>
Surely the pioneering the earlier guilds did should be to their advantage and not used as an example to give the guilds following them new and easier rules to join them on that rotation.<br>
<br>
For a guild currently on a rotation, I don't think many people really care if another guild joins that rotation. Everyone is used to the fact that as time goes on, more and more guilds will be killing each mob, What people don't want to be seeing is mobs going to waste. This is most noticable on AoW because after someone fails, it is 5 days before anyone can try again. Let's look at the current situation where both VoF and FK are looking at trying AoW and joining the rotation. If these guilds rushed to the mob each time Statue was being killed, no one else would see AoW again until both those guilds were on the rotation.<br>
<br>
Part of the advantage of being on a rotation is it is a guaranteed shot. You don't have to camp the mob so you can engage as soon as it spawns. You have the ability to check when it is up and then go and kill it. For this reasonl there is often plenty of hours of a mob being up before the guild on rotation for it will go there and attempt it. For this reason, there will always be time windows for mobs to be attempted by new guilds. If these guilds tried these mobs all night, and then came back the next night to try again it would be unfair as they are barring the rotation guilds from shots at their mobs.<br>
<br>
Rules are made to protect guilds currently on a rotation and also those who will be on that rotation in the future. If everyone abides by them, things run smoothly. Otherwise, problems arise and everyone will end up unhappy.<br>
<br>
Thun <p>Thundax Stormkeeper<br>
